_**Skin Wars**_ is a [body painting](/wiki/Body_painting "Body painting")
reality competition hosted by [Rebecca Romijn](/wiki/Rebecca_Romijn "Rebecca
Romijn") that premiered on [Game Show Network](/wiki/Game_Show_Network "Game
Show Network") on August 6, 2014.[1]

Skin Wars Contestants on the series perform challenges containing [body
painting](/wiki/Body_painting "Body painting") each episode. At the end of
each episode, one contestant is eliminated and told "It's time to wash off
your canvas."[2]

## Production[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Skin_Wars&action=edit&section=1 "Edit
section: Production")]

On September 12, 2013, GSN ordered eight episodes of the series,[1][2] making
it GSN's first television show devoted to body art.[2] On February 4, 2014,
GSN announced Rebecca Romijn as host of _Skin Wars_ , with [RuPaul
Charles](/wiki/RuPaul "RuPaul"), Craig Tracy and [Robin
Slonina](/wiki/Robin_Barcus_Slonina "Robin Barcus Slonina") serving as
judges.[3]

The series premiered on GSN August 6, 2014.[4] That same night, the network
also began airing an online series entitled _Skin Wars: The Naked Truth with
Kandee Johnson_ airing immediately after _Skin Wars_ on DOOR3, GSN's
[YouTube](/wiki/YouTube "YouTube") channel targeted toward 18- to 25-year-
olds. The series features commentary from Johnson as well as highlights from
that night's episode and a "Skinterview" with one of the contestants.[5]

On September 30, 2014, GSN announced plans to air a ten-episode second season
of _Skin Wars_ with Romijn and all three judges returning to reprise their
respective roles.[6] The second season premiered June 10, 2015.[7]

A spinoff called _Skin Wars: Fresh Paint_ hosted by [RuPaul](/wiki/RuPaul
"RuPaul") aired as a special on August 26, 2015. It featured six highly
accomplished artists, each at the top of their game, as they leave their
comfort zones to compete in body painting for the first time. The artists must
conquer three difficult challenges as they are mentored by three top artists
from the first season, Dutch Bihary, Lawrence "Gear" Duran and Season One
champion, Natalie Fletcher. As the artists work closely with their body
painting mentors they try to quickly master the craft and win the $10,000
prize and become champion. It premiered to 456,000 viewers.[8] Later, it
became a series itself, premiering on June 15, 2016.[9]

On August 27, 2015, GSN renewed the series for a third season.[10]

## International
broadcast[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Skin_Wars&action=edit&section=11 "Edit
section: International broadcast")]

In [Australia](/wiki/Australia "Australia"), the series premiered on
[LifeStyle You](/wiki/LifeStyle_You "LifeStyle You") on May 26, 2015.[14] All
three seasons are now available on Netflix.

In [Canada](/wiki/Canada "Canada"), the series aired on [GameTV](/wiki/GameTV
"GameTV") in 2015.[15]

In the [United Kingdom](/wiki/United_Kingdom "United Kingdom"), the series
premiered on [truTV UK](/wiki/TruTV_\(UK_and_Ireland\) "TruTV \(UK and
Ireland\)") in 2015.[16]

In [Brazil](/wiki/Brazil "Brazil"), the show's first season has been broadcast
on [Multishow](/wiki/Multishow "Multishow") since February, 2016 and since
2017 on [E!](/wiki/E! "E!")  
In [South Africa](/wiki/South_Africa "South Africa") it broadcasts on [Sony
Max](/wiki/Sony_Max "Sony Max").  
In [India](/wiki/India "India"),the show's first season has been broadcast on
[FYI TV18](/wiki/FYI_TV18 "FYI TV18") since 2016.
